HEADWORD: Wire-puller
<hw>Wire"-pull`er</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>One who pulls the wires, as of a puppet; hence, one
who uses secret influence (i.e. pulls wires or strings) for his own
ends; an intriguer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Political <qex>wire-pullers</qex> and convention packers.</q>
<rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wire-pulling</ent>⟦br⟧
